abstract: ST. PETERSBURG Fla., April 16 (AP)--Fourth-seeded Allen Fox of Los Angeles defeated the defending champion, Nicola Pilic of Yugoslavia, 6-3, 3-6, 6-4, 4-6 6-3, today in the final of the Masters tennis tournament.
headline_main: Fox Takes Masters Crown By Beating Pilic in 5 Sets

abstract: DICK and Tom Smothers, who can't even stand the sight of bloody battles painted on a lunch box, are suddenly in the midst of a two-front war; winning against the enemy and losing on home base. The whole scene makes them ponder a question they had never before seriously entertained...

WAYNE, Pa., April 15--In St. David's Episcopal Church here this afternoon, Miss Barbara Barnes Wilmerding, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. David R. Wilmerding of Berwyn, became the bride of Robert Wallace Macleod. He is the son of Mrs. Alexander Macleod of Dedham, Mass., and the late Mr. Macleod.
headline_main: Barbara Barnes Wilmerding Married to Robert Macleod
headline_print_headline: Barbara Barnes Wilmerding Married to Robert Macleod

abstract: Harry Miklowitz, who retired in 1952 as chairman of the boys health-education department of William Cullen Bryant High School, Long Island City, Queens, died Wednesday in the Towers Hotel, Miami, after a long illness. He was 71 years old and lived at 11 West 81st Street here.
